P&G for a break before pursuing her PH.D and after two years she fell in love with the job and forgot about getting her PH.D. P&G became her home. Some of her many ideas include the signing of Queen Latifah, Ellen DeGeneres, and Drew Barrymore as brand ambassadors, and the launch of several best-sellers including Simply Ageless foundation and Lash Blast mascara.   Today, COVERGIRL is the nation’s fastest growing cosmetics brand and the “hottest” cosmetics brand in 2009 . In recognition of all her achievements, Women’s Wear Daily awarded Esi with the “2008 Marketer of the Year” award; Advertising Age recognized her as one of 13 “Women to Watch” in 2009; and Cosmetics Executive Women (CEW), a non-profit organization of over 4,000 executives and managers in the beauty industry presented Esi with its highest honor, the “2009 Achiever Award.Today Mrs. Bracey oversees the Cover Girl and Max Factor brands, which generate more than $2 billion in retail sales, and supervises over 1,000 employees. Her leadership, creativity,diversity and individuality inspire achievement, “out-of-the-box” thinking and passion. many describe her as a top-level professional, dynamic, engaging and charismatic speaker and find her professional career to be incredibly inspiring. MRS.EGGLESTON BRACEY NOWON TOP OF HER GAMEACHIEVEMENTS AND RECOGNITIONSOURCEShttp://innocosevents.com/2013/09/01/esi-eggleston-bracey-vice-president-general-manager-global-pg-cosmetics-innovation-branding-and-operations/http://internalmarket.wordpress.com/2012/02/12/master-class-pgs-esi-eggleston-bracey/Full transcriptMore presentations by
    
        
